{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01D1bRwTwAbKmHNKYG84nxai","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. The app:\n- Label: `app: demo-app`\n- Port: 5678\n- Serves at \"/\" with \"hello\" content\n\nI need to:\n1. Create a Service targeting `app: demo-app` on port 5678\n2. Create an Ingress that routes `demo.example.com/app` to the Service\n\nBut there's a catch: the app only serves \"/\", not \"/app\". So I need the ingress to rewrite the path from \"/app\" to \"/\" using nginx annotations.\n\nThe nginx ingress rewrite annotation is:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /`\n- path: `/app`\n\nThis will handle the path rewriting cleanly without needing complex regex patterns.\n\nNow I'm setting up the Service and Ingress resources...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1036,"cache_read_input_tokens":28428,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1036},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"141d2452-9df0-4ba2-be35-1c587ff45c04","uuid":"baa63cec-f6cd-424f-8ca6-f8be7eb7e8eb","request_id":"req_011CcaeVadk5Ty1eawp2oS72"}
